<emphasis box="[136,313,1058,1079]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">Anethum pusillum</emphasis>
All.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Allioni, C." box="[370,538,1058,1080]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" pagination="53 - 96" refId="ref1383" refString="Allioni, C. (1773) Auctarium ad Synopsim Methodicam Stirpium Horti Regii Taurinensis. Torino, 44 pp. [Pre-printed from: Melange de Philosophie et de Mathematique dela Societe Royale de Turin pour les annees 1770 - 1773, V: 53 - 96. 1774]" type="book chapter" year="1773">Allioni 1773: 28</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="206" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1058,1152]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="TO" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
Type (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[620,889,1058,1080]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">lectotype, designated here</emphasis>
- or perhaps 
<typeStatus box="[1024,1113,1058,1080]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">holotype</typeStatus>
): [No locality] “ 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Anethum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="pusillum" subSpecies="segetum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">Anethum pusillum segetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.” Allioni Collection (
<collectionCode box="[504,537,1095,1116]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">TO</collectionCode>
[without number])
</materialsCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[736,795,1094,1116]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,2046,2068]" captionTargetBox="[226,1362,350,2019]" captionTargetId="figure-138@1.[226,1362,350,2019]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lectotype of Anethum pusillum All. (TO, Allioni Collection [without number]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6821001" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6821001/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="206" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1058,1152]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">
[= 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus (1753: 263)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="263" authorityYear="1753" box="[837,1264,1094,1116]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Anethum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graveolens">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[837,1044,1094,1116]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">Anethum graveolens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[1051,1264,1094,1116]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" refId="ref1933" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1753) Species Plantarum. Vol. I. Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae [Stockholm], 560 pp." type="book" year="1753">Linnaeus (1753: 263)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<typeStatus box="[1276,1372,1095,1116]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">Lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Jansen, P. C. M." pageId="0" pageNumber="206" refId="ref1783" refString="Jansen, P. C. M. (1981) Spices, condiments and medicinal plants of Ethiopia: Their taxonomy and agricultural significance. Centre for Agricultural Publishing and Documentation, Wageningen, 327 pp." type="book" year="1981">Jansen 1981: 34</bibRefCitation>
): Herb. Linn. No. 371.1 (LINN)].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="206" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1201,1549]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis box="[136,389,1201,1225]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">Note on the typification</emphasis>
:— 
<bibRefCitation author="Dal Vesco, G." box="[422,611,1201,1225]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" pagination="91 - 99" refId="ref1521" refString="Dal Vesco, G. (1986) Tipi nell'erbario Allioni. Allionia 27: 91 - 99." type="journal article" year="1986">Dal Vesco (1986)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName box="[715,837,1201,1225]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Anethum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pusillum">
<emphasis box="[715,837,1201,1225]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">A. pusillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
among those species represented in Allioni collection by more than one sheet. Actually, we were able to find only 
<specimenCount box="[740,886,1237,1261]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
with that name in the Allioni collection (TO), but we cannot conclude that 
<typeStatus box="[366,540,1273,1297]" isOtherTypeStatus="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">other specimens</typeStatus>
do not exist and cannot be found in the future. That’s why we choose this specimen as the 
<typeStatus box="[204,305,1309,1333]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1201,1549]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis box="[189,359,1345,1368]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">Taxonomic note</emphasis>
: The observation of the unripe fruits in the specimen, selected in this work as the 
<typeStatus box="[1249,1350,1345,1369]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">lectotype</typeStatus>
, suggests it corresponds to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[322,469,1381,1405]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Anethum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graveolens">
<emphasis box="[322,469,1381,1405]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">A. graveolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so that 
<taxonomicName box="[560,682,1381,1405]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Anethum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pusillum">
<emphasis box="[560,682,1381,1405]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">A. pusillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not synonymous with “ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus 1771: 219) Moris (1841: 43)" authorityName="Moris" authorityPageNumber="43" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityPageNumber="219" baseAuthorityYear="1771" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Ridolfia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis box="[963,1143,1381,1405]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">Ridolfia segetum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[1157,1373,1381,1405]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" refId="ref1958" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1771) Mantissa Plantarum Altera. Generum editionis VI &amp; specierum editionis II. Holmiae [Stockholm], 587 pp." type="book" year="1771">Linnaeus 1771: 219</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Moris, J. H." pageId="0" pageNumber="206" refId="ref2010" refString="Moris, J. H. (1841) Enumeratio seminum regii horti botanici Taurinensis an. 1841. Typographia Regia, Torino, 44 pp." type="book" year="1841">Moris (1841: 43)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
” as proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chiovenda, E." box="[447,646,1417,1441]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" pagination="15 - 23" refId="ref1480" refString="Chiovenda, E. (1912) Della priorita di alcuni nomi specifici di piante contenuti nell' &quot; Auctarium ad Synopsim Methodicam Stirpium Horti Regi Taurinensis &quot; dell'Allioni pubblicato nel 1774. Annali di Botanica 10: 15 - 23." type="journal article" year="1912">Chiovenda (1912)</bibRefCitation>
, dubitatively by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dandy, J. E." box="[833,987,1417,1441]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" pagination="617 - 626" refId="ref1540" refString="Dandy, J. E. (1970) Annotated List of the New Names Published in Allioni's &quot; Auctarium ad Synopsim Stirpium Horti Reg. Taurinensis &quot;. Taxon 19 (4): 617 - 626. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1218957" type="journal article" year="1970">Dandy (1970)</bibRefCitation>
, and more recently by 
<bibRefCitation author="POWO" box="[1244,1403,1417,1441]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" refId="ref2059" refString="POWO (2022) Plants of the World Online. Facilitated by the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. Published on the Internet; http: // www. plantsoftheworldonline. org / (Retrieved 5 March 2022)." type="url" year="2022">POWO (2022)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="WCVP" box="[136,295,1453,1477]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" refId="ref2201" refString="WCVP (2022) World Checklist of Vascular Plants, version 2. 0. Facilitated by the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. Published on the Internet; http: // wcvp. science. kew. org / (Retrieved 5 March 2022)" type="url" year="2022">WCVP (2022)</bibRefCitation>
. However, this latter name has to be cited more correctly as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gussone 1827: 346) Moris (1841: 43)" authorityName="Moris" authorityPageNumber="43" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Gussone" baseAuthorityPageNumber="346" baseAuthorityYear="1827" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Ridolfia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis box="[961,1143,1453,1477]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">Ridolfia segetum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gussone, G." box="[1159,1371,1453,1477]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" refId="ref1683" refString="Gussone, G., (1827) Florae Siculae Prodromus sive Plantarum in Sicilia Ulteriori Nascentium Enumeratio Secundum Systema Linnaeanum Disposita, Vol. 1. Regia Typographia, Neapoli [Naples], 592 + 11 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 6700" type="book" year="1827">Gussone 1827: 346</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Moris, J. H." pageId="0" pageNumber="206" refId="ref2010" refString="Moris, J. H. (1841) Enumeratio seminum regii horti botanici Taurinensis an. 1841. Typographia Regia, Torino, 44 pp." type="book" year="1841">Moris (1841: 43)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see below). Incidentally, also the other 
<specimenCount box="[691,850,1489,1513]" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moris" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Gussone" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[888,1006,1489,1512]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Ridolfia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis box="[888,1006,1489,1512]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">A. segetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Allioni collection (TO) have to be referred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[255,401,1525,1549]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Anethum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graveolens">
<emphasis box="[255,401,1525,1549]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="206">A. graveolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
